prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Provide a web-based bus ticket reservation function",
      "evidence_quote": "providing a web-based bus ticket reservation function where a customer can buy a bus ticket through the online system"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow customers to check availability and types of buses online",
      "evidence_quote": "enabling customers to check the availability and types of buses online"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Enable customers to check time departure for every Indian Tourist Centre (ITC) bus",
      "evidence_quote": "Customer can check the time departure for every Indian Tourist Centre (ITC) bus through the system"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Ease bus ticket payment by obtaining a bank pin after payments is made to various designated banks",
      "evidence_quote": "easing bus ticket payment by obtaining a bank pin after payments is made to the various designated banks"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow customers to cancel their reservation",
      "evidence_quote": "the ability of customers to cancel their reservation"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Provide admin user privileges for updating and cancelling payment, route and vehicle records",
      "evidence_quote": "admin user privileges in updating and cancelling payment, route and vehicle records"
    }
  ]
}

